    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-15T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="130"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.24/618b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-15T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 15, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>263. The Navy Department has agreed to increase to $3,700,000 the amount of naval
                    matériel to be delivered to Cuba under the proposed lend-lease arrangement; of
                    this $300,000 can be delivered during the next 12 months. The War Department has
                    agreed to increase to $3,500,000, the amount of military matériel to be
                    delivered; of this $1,000,000 would be made available during the next 12 months.
                    The Cuban <pb facs="0130" n="122" xml:id="pg_122"/> Government will be expected
                    to repay a total of $4,200,000 at the rate of $700,000 a year for 6 years. The
                    Cuban Ambassador has been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
